cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.HC 

The paper discusses state-of-the-art methods for palmprint recognition, which involves computer vision techniques such as feature extraction and matching algorithms. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of palmprints on consumer devices, which suggests a focus on mobile computing and human-computer interaction, leading to possible sub-categories of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses the use of datasets for palmprint recognition, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
